  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "raadsr_inst": "Please read each statement below and choose the answer that best fits your experiences during social interactions.",
      "r1": "I am a sympathetic person.",
      "r2": "I often use words and phrases from movies and television in conversations.",
      "r3": "I am often surprised when others tell me I have been rude.",
      "r4": "Sometimes I talk too loudly or too softly, and I am not aware of it.",
      "r5": "I often don't know how to act in social situations.",
      "r6": "I can \"put myself in other people's shoes.\"",
      "r7": "I have a hard time figuring out what some phrases mean, like \"you are the apple of my eye.\"",
      "r8": "I only like to talk to people who share my special interests.",
      "r9": "I focus on details rather than the overall idea.",
      "r10": "I always notice how food feels in my mouth. This is more important to me than how it tastes.",
      "r11": "I miss my best friends or family when we are apart for a long time.",
      "r12": "Sometimes I offend others by saying what I am thinking, even if I don't mean to.",
      "r13": "I only like to think and talk about a few things that interest me.",
      "r14": "I'd rather go out to eat in a restaurant by myself than with someone I know.",
      "r15": "I cannot imagine what it would be like to be someone else.",
      "r16": "I have been told that I am clumsy or uncoordinated.",
      "r17": "Others consider me odd or different.",
      "r18": "I understand when friends need to be comforted.",
      "r19": "I am very sensitive to the way my clothes feel when I touch them. How they feel is more important to me than how they look.",
      "r20": "I like to copy the way certain people speak and act. It helps me appear more normal.",
      "r21": "It can be very intimidating for me to talk to more than one person at the same time.",
      "r22": "I have to \"act normal\" to please other people and make them like me.",
      "r23": "Meeting new people is usually easy for me.",
      "r24": "I get highly confused when someone interrupts me when I am talking about something I am very interested in.",
      "r25": "It is difficult for me to understand how other people are feeling when we are talking.",
      "r26": "I like having a conversation with several people, for instance around a dinner table, at school or at work.",
      "r27": "I take things too literally, so I often miss what people are trying to say.",
      "r28": "It is very difficult for me to understand when someone is embarrassed or jealous.",
      "r29": "Some ordinary textures that do not bother others feel very offensive when they touch my skin.",
      "r30": "I get extremely upset when the way I like to do things is suddenly changed.",
      "r31": "I have never wanted or needed to have what other people call an \"intimate relationship.\"",
      "r32": "It is difficult for me to start and stop a conversation. I need to keep going until I am finished.",
      "r33": "I speak with a normal rhythm.",
      "r34": "The same sound, color, or texture can suddenly change from very sensitive to very dull.",
      "r35": "The phrase \"I've got you under my skin\" makes me very uncomfortable.",
      "r36": "Sometimes the sound of a word or a high-pitched noise can be painful to my ears.",
      "r37": "I am an understanding type of person.",
      "r38": "I do not connect with characters in movies and cannot feel what they feel.",
      "r39": "I cannot tell when someone is flirting with me.",
      "r40": "I can see in my mind in exact detail things that I am interested in.",
      "r41": "I keep lists of things that interest me, even when they have no practical use (for example sports statistics, train schedules, calendar dates, historical facts and dates).",
      "r42": "When I feel overwhelmed by my senses, I have to isolate myself to shut them down.",
      "r43": "I like to talk things over with my friends.",
      "r44": "I cannot tell if someone is interested or bored with what I am saying.",
      "r45": "It can be very hard to read someone's face, hand and body movements when they are talking.",
      "r46": "The same thing (like clothes or temperatures) can feel very different to me at different times.",
      "r47": "I feel very comfortable with dating or being in social situations with others.",
      "r48": "I try to be as helpful as I can when other people tell me their personal problems.",
      "r49": "I have been told that I have an unusual voice (for example flat, monotone, childish, or high-pitched).",
      "r50": "Sometimes a thought or a subject gets stuck in my mind and I have to talk about it even if no one is interested.",
      "r51": "I do certain things with my hands over and over again (like flapping, twirling sticks or strings, waving things by my eyes).",
      "r52": "I have never been interested in what most of the people I know consider interesting.",
      "r53": "I am considered a compassionate type of person.",
      "r54": "I get along with other people by following a set of specific rules that help me look normal.",
      "r55": "It is very difficult for me to work and function in groups.",
      "r56": "When I am talking to someone, it is hard to change the subject. If the other person does so, I can get very upset and confused.",
      "r57": "Sometimes I have to cover my ears to block out painful noises (like vacuum cleaners or people talking too much or too loudly).",
      "r58": "I can chat and make small talk with people.",
      "r59": "Sometimes things that should feel painful are not (for instance when I hurt myself or burn my hand on a stove).",
      "r60": "When talking to someone, I have a hard time telling when it is my turn to talk or to listen.",
      "r61": "I am considered a loner by those who know me best.",
      "r62": "I usually speak in a normal tone.",
      "r63": "I like things to be exactly the same day after day and even small changes in my routines upset me.",
      "r64": "How to make friends and socialize is a mystery to me.",
      "r65": "It calms me to spin around or to rock in a chair when I am feeling stressed.",
